IMPLEMENTATION STEPS:

1. SETUP PHASE
   a. Initialize Astro project: `npm create astro@latest`
   b. Install dependencies: astro-htmx, supabase, rxdb, typescript
   c. Create Supabase project and tables (see DATABASE SCHEMA below)
   d. Set up environment variables (.env)

2. DATABASE SCHEMA
   Create these tables in Supabase:
   
   -- Schools (multi-tenant)
   CREATE TABLE schools (
     id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
     name TEXT NOT NULL,
     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
   );

   -- Users (admin, teacher, parent)
   CREATE TABLE users (
     id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
     school_id UUID REFERENCES schools(id),
     email TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
     password_hash TEXT,
     role TEXT CHECK (role IN ('admin', 'teacher', 'parent')) NOT NULL,
     first_name TEXT, last_name TEXT,
     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now(),
     updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
   );

   -- Students
   CREATE TABLE students (
     id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
     school_id UUID REFERENCES schools(id),
     first_name TEXT NOT NULL,
     last_name TEXT NOT NULL,
     email TEXT,
     enrollment_date DATE,
     grade_level INT,
     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now(),
     updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
   );

   -- Classes
   CREATE TABLE classes (
     id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
     school_id UUID REFERENCES schools(id),
     teacher_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
     name TEXT NOT NULL,
     subject TEXT,
     grade_level INT,
     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
   );

   -- Attendance
   CREATE TABLE attendance (
     id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
     school_id UUID REFERENCES schools(id),
     student_id UUID REFERENCES students(id),
     class_id UUID REFERENCES classes(id),
     date DATE NOT NULL,
     status TEXT CHECK (status IN ('present', 'absent', 'late', 'excused')) NOT NULL,
     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
   );

   -- Grades
   CREATE TABLE grades (
     id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
     school_id UUID REFERENCES schools(id),
     student_id UUID REFERENCES students(id),
     class_id UUID REFERENCES classes(id),
     grade DECIMAL(5,2) NOT NULL,
     grading_period TEXT,
     created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now(),
     updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
   );

   CREATE INDEX idx_school_id ON students(school_id);
   CREATE INDEX idx_school_id ON users(school_id);
   CREATE INDEX idx_student_id ON attendance(student_id);

3. RxDB SETUP
   a. Create RxDB database instance with offline-first sync
   b. Define schemas matching Supabase tables
   c. Set up replication plugin to sync with Supabase API
   d. Persist to IndexedDB (browser) + localStorage fallback

4. AUTH LAYER
   a. Login page (email/password)
   b. JWT token storage in secure httpOnly cookie (server-side)
   c. Role-based access control (RBAC) middleware
   d. Logout functionality

5. FRONTEND COMPONENTS
   a. Dashboard: role-specific views (admin sees all, teacher sees their classes, parent sees their child)
   b. Student list: searchable, paginated (HTMX for filtering)
   c. Attendance form: quick mark/update with HTMX auto-save
   d. Grade entry: table view, inline edit with HTMX
   e. Reports: PDF export for parents (via server-side generation)

6. API ENDPOINTS (in src/pages/api/)
   - POST /api/auth/login
   - POST /api/auth/logout
   - GET /api/students?school_id=X
   - POST /api/attendance (create/update)
   - GET /api/grades?student_id=X
   - POST /api/sync (RxDB pull replication)
   - GET /api/sync (RxDB push replication)

7. OFFLINE SYNC STRATEGY
   a. RxDB watches for changes locally
   b. When online, POST to /api/sync to push changes
   c. GET /api/sync periodically to pull remote changes
   c. Conflict resolution: last-write-wins (with timestamps)

NICE-TO-HAVES:
- Email notifications for grades/attendance (SendGrid)
- Parent portal: view child's progress in real-time
- Mobile-responsive dashboard
- Dark mode toggle
- Bulk CSV import for students/grades
- Analytics: attendance trends, grade distribution

IMPORTANT NOTES:
- Keep JS minimal: use HTMX for interactivity, Astro for SSR
- Optimize for low bandwidth: compress assets, lazy-load images
- Test offline mode: disable network in DevTools, verify RxDB works
- Security: sanitize inputs, validate on server, use prepared statements
- Performance: measure Core Web Vitals, aim for <3s FCP on 3G

START WITH:
1. Set up Astro project with Supabase credentials
2. Create all Supabase tables (run SQL in Dashboard)
3. Build login page + auth middleware
4. Create student dashboard (read-only first)
5. Add attendance form (HTMX + RxDB sync)
6. Then expand: grades, parent portal, reports

